IP ADDRESSES

Layer 3 : iPv4/6

-inet : decimal(ipV4)
 -128   64   32   16   8   4   2   1
 -Possible number of IP addresses 4.3 billion(2^32)
   -Has been used up already
   -Hence we use NAT(Network address translation)

 -192.168.0.0 to 192.168.255.255 : Private IP address
  -No.of networks is 20197151 however no. of hosts per network is 254




USE arp-scan -l TO LIST ALL IP ADDRESSES CONNECTED TO YOUR NETWORK



    

-inet6 : hexadecimal(ipV6)
 -Possible number of IP addresses 2^128
